Police on Thursday arrested four people suspected to be behind a spate of robberies in the Western region. The officers from Butula Sub-County Criminal Investigations Officer and Samia Police Station conducted a series of operations which led to the arrest of the suspects. "The operation led to the arrest of four suspects believed to have been behind a spate of robberies and insecurity in the region," NPS inspector general of police Hillary Mutyambai said. The operation was conducted in Samia, Busia County and Ugenya, Siaya County The police are said to have received a tipoff from the locals who spotted one of the suspects. One of the suspects was arrested at Masati Obeti trading centre in Ugenya sub-county. After interrogations by the police, the suspect named the others leading to their arrest at Agenga in Samia. "An assortment of items were found at the premises of the suspects which included, a motorcycle, Government of Kenya Digital learning tablet, police uniform, several sacks of sugar, cooking oil among other items," Mutyambai added. The suspects are currently being detained at Sioport Police Station ahead of their arraignment. He added the NPS officers are scaling up security in the area and urged the public to remain vigilant and report suspicious persons and sharing of information to assist the law enforcement teams. On Sunday, a businessman was shot by unknown people next to his residence around Breeze Hotel in Busia County. Busia deputy county commissioner Kipchumba Ruto said, “We have enhanced patrols across the county to ensure security and we urge residents to cooperate and volunteer any information to the relevant authorities.’’